<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="88" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,158,933]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">
—The genus includes two main clades according to Larridon 
<emphasis box="[994,1049,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">et al.</emphasis>
(2018) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Merklinger, F. F. &amp; Bohnert, T. &amp; Arakaki, M. &amp; Weigend, M. &amp; Quandt, D." box="[1179,1447,762,788]" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" pagination="184 - 199" refId="ref18131" refString="Merklinger, F. F., Bohnert, T., Arakaki, M., Weigend, M. &amp; Quandt, D. (2021) Luebert F. Quaternary diversification of a columnar cactus in the driest place on earth. American Journal of Botany 108: 184 - 199. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / ajb 2.1608" type="journal article" year="2021">
Merklinger 
<emphasis box="[1310,1365,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">et al.</emphasis>
(2021)
</bibRefCitation>
. The two groups are morphologically and phylogenetically supported and clearly associated with geographical changes in the 
<collectingRegion box="[205,384,834,861]" country="Chile" name="Atacama" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Atacama Desert</collectingRegion>
(a proposed key is reported below). According to the results of the phylogenetic analyses three former species-complexes were resolved: 
<taxonomicName authority="Phil." authorityName="Phil." box="[616,866,870,896]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Eulychnia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acida">
<emphasis box="[616,801,870,896]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">Eulychnia acida</emphasis>
Phil.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Phil." authorityName="Phil." box="[879,1088,870,896]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Eulychnia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="breviflora">
<emphasis box="[879,1023,870,896]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">E. breviflora</emphasis>
Phil.
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(K. Schum.) Britton &amp; Rose." authorityName="Britton &amp; Rose." baseAuthorityName="K. Schum." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Eriosyce" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="iquiquensis">
<emphasis box="[1151,1312,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="88">E. iquiquensis</emphasis>
(K.Schum.) Britton &amp; Rose.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
